HEADWORD: Night terrors
<hw>Night terrors</hw>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A sudden awakening
associated with a sensation of terror, occurring in children, esp. those
of unstable nervous constitution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

